    <div class="calc-layout">
      <div class="calc-main">
        <h1>% Percentage Calculator</h1>
        <p class="calc-intro">Calculate any percentage instantly — three types of percentage problems solved in one place.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:1rem">1. What is X% of Y?</p>
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>Percentage (%)</label><input type="number" id="p1-pct" placeholder="15" oninput="calcP1()"></div>
            <div><label>Of number (Y)</label><input type="number" id="p1-val" placeholder="200" oninput="calcP1()"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-box" id="p1-res">Enter the values</div>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:1rem">
          <p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:1rem">2. X is what % of Y?</p>
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>X (part)</label><input type="number" id="p2-x" placeholder="30" oninput="calcP2()"></div>
            <div><label>Y (total)</label><input type="number" id="p2-y" placeholder="200" oninput="calcP2()"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-box" id="p2-res">Enter the values</div>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top:1rem">
          <p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:1rem">3. Percentage change from X to Y</p>
          <div class="row-2">
            <div><label>Original value (X)</label><input type="number" id="p3-x" placeholder="80" oninput="calcP3()"></div>
            <div><label>New value (Y)</label><input type="number" id="p3-y" placeholder="100" oninput="calcP3()"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-box" id="p3-res">Enter the values</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is a percentage?</h2>
          <p>A percentage is a number expressed as a fraction of 100. The symbol % means "per hundred". Percentages are used everywhere — from shop discounts and tax rates to statistics, grades and financial returns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I calculate 20% of 150?</summary>
            <p>Multiply 150 by 20 and divide by 100. Result: 30. Or multiply by 0.20 directly.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I calculate a percentage increase?</summary>
            <p>Use section 3 above. Subtract original from new value, divide by original, multiply by 100. From 80 to 100 is (100−80)÷80×100 = 25% increase.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I work out what percentage one number is of another?</summary>
            <p>Use section 2 above. Divide the part by the total and multiply by 100. For example, 30 is what % of 200? 30÷200×100 = 15%.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Related calculators</h3>
